  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Although we're running quite a number of full nodes, the dev team isn't really hammering the light client as much as we should. A possible starting point would be to create 3 Travis nightly cron jobs that just spin up Geth instances and try to sync to mainnet, Rospten and Rinkeby with a 5 minute timeout. The idea would be to detect sync issues and anomalies during development, not half an hour before release when I do some sanity test runs.",
